      <abstract displayLabel="Summary">The macOS Security Compliance Project (mSCP) provides resources that
                system administrators, security professionals, security policy authors, information
                security officers, and auditors can leverage to secure and assess macOS desktop and
                laptop system security in an automated way. This publication introduces the mSCP and
                gives an overview of the resources available from the projectâ€™s GitHub site, which
                is continuously curated and updated to support each new release of macOS. The GitHub
                site provides practical, actionable recommendations in the form of secure baselines
                and associated rules. This publication also describes use cases for leveraging the
                mSCP content. Updates from the previous version of this publication mainly involve
                the new mSCP capability to create a custom benchmark by tailoring a
                baseline.</abstract>
